get.summary: Ping the Element to confirm that the Hub Element has a heartbeat.  If the Element does not have a heartbeat, an error message will be returned.
Search for boards, lists, cards, members, etc. See docs here: https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/trello/rest/api-group-search/#api-search-get

parameters.name: Authorization
parameters.description: The authorization tokens. The format for the header value is 'Element <token>, User <user secret>'

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: The search query with a length of 1 to 16384 characters

parameters.name: boardId
parameters.description: `mine` or a comma-separated list of Board IDs

parameters.name: idOrganizations
parameters.description: A comma-separated list of Organization IDs

parameters.name: idCards
parameters.description: A comma-separated list of Card IDs

parameters.name: modelTypes
parameters.description: What type or types of Trello objects you want to search. `all` or a comma-separated list of: actions, boards, cards, members, organizations. Default: all

parameters.name: board_fields
parameters.description: `all` or a comma-separated list of: closed, dateLastActivity, dateLastView, desc, descData, idOrganization, invitations, invited, labelNames, memberships, name, pinned, powerUps, prefs, shortLink, shortUrl, starred, subscribed, url. Default: name,idOrganization

parameters.name: boards_limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of boards returned. Default: 10, Maximum: 1000

parameters.name: card_fields
parameters.description: `all` or a comma-separated list of: badges, checkItemStates, closed, dateLastActivity, desc, descData, due, email, idAttachmentCover, idBoard, idChecklists, idLabels, idList, idMembers, idMembersVoted, idShort, labels, manualCoverAttachment, name, pos, shortLink, shortUrl, subscribed, url

parameters.name: cards_limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of cards to return. Maximum: 1000

parameters.name: cards_page
parameters.description: The page of results for cards. Maximum: 100

parameters.name: card_board
parameters.description: Whether to include the parent board with card results. Default: false

parameters.name: card_members
parameters.description: Whether to include member objects with card results. Default: false

parameters.name: card_stickers
parameters.description: Whether to include sticker objects with card results. Default: false

parameters.name: card_attachments
parameters.description: Whether to include attachment objects with card results. A boolean value (true or false) or cover for only card cover attachments. Default: false

parameters.name: organization_fields
parameters.description: `all` or a comma-separated list of billableMemberCount, desc, descData, displayName, idBoards, invitations, invited, logoHash, memberships, name, powerUps, prefs, premiumFeatures, products, url, website. Default: name,displayName

parameters.name: organizations_limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of teams to return. Maximum 1000. Default: 10, Format: int32

parameters.name: member_fields
parameters.description: `all` or a comma-separated list of: avatarHash, bio, bioData, confirmed, fullName, idPremOrgsAdmin, initials, memberType, products, status, url, username. Default: avatarHash,fullName,initials,username,confirmed

parameters.name: members_limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of members to return. Maximum 1000. Default: 10, Format: int32

parameters.name: partial
parameters.description: By default, Trello searches for each word in your query against exactly matching words within Member content. Specifying partial to be true means that we will look for content that starts with any of the words in your query. If you are looking for a Card titled "My Development Status Report", by default you would need to search for "Development". If you have partial enabled, you will be able to search for "dev" but not "velopment". Default: false

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of resources to return in a given page
The next page cursor, taken from the response header: `elements-next-page-token`
